METRO DIGEST LOCAL NEWS IN BRIEF: SUPERMARKET MANAGER SLAIN DURING HOLDUP 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Police were seeking leads Tuesday in the Monday evening slaying of the manager 
of an Inglewood supermarket, who was shot and killed by three gunmen during a 
holdup. 
</P>
<P>
Younis Awadallah, 42, of Torrance, was shot in the head about 8:30 p.m. Monday 
inside City Farm Market at the border of Inglewood and the unincorporated 
Lennox area, police said. 
</P>
<P>
He died two hours later at Daniel Freeman Memorial Hospital. 
</P>
<P>
Police said the three men ran from the store with an undetermined amount of 
cash. 
</P>
<P>
Although there were several other workers and customers in the market at the 
time of the robbery, police said they did not offer descriptions of the 
robbers. 
</P>
<P>
A worker said the store has not had a problem with holdups in the past. 
</P>
