<TEXT>
<P>
Liege May Sell Picasso: The debt-ridden city of Liege, Belgium, is considering 
the sale of a Picasso masterpiece to keep its museums open. 
</P>
<P>
"Either we sell this Picasso or we have to close a dozen museums for lack of 
funds," culture alderman Hector Magotte told the daily newspaper Het Belang van 
Limburg. The city council hopes to make $57 million from the sale of the 1903 
painting of the Soler family, a masterpiece of Picasso's "Blue Period." The 
council will make a decision on the sale next month. BETH KLEID 
