<P>
PEOPLE: RAIDEN NAMED EXECUTIVE VP AT COAST SAVINGS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Norman H. Raiden, 57, general counsel of the Federal Home Loan Bank Board from 
1983 to 1985, will join Coast Savings &amp; Loan as executive vice president 
over the legal and subsidiaries groups. 
</P>
<P>
Raiden resigned as a senior partner in the McKenna, Conner &amp; Cuneo law firm 
in Los Angeles to accept the new position. 
</P>
<P>
In his new position, Raiden will oversee legal activities, mergers and 
acquisitions, major real estate projects and subsidiaries offering insurance 
agency and business credit services. Robert A. Scott, senior vice president, 
remains general counsel of Coast and its holding company. 
</P>
<P>
Raiden succeeds William S. Bradway III, 43, who resigned to move to New England 
for family reasons. 
</P>
