<P>
PEOPLE: SELLERS TO TAKE OVER AT MACY'S DIVISION 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A new president and chief operating officer has been named for the Macy's 
South/Bullock's division of R. H. Macy &amp; Co. 
</P>
<P>
The incoming president is Mark S. Sellers, 38, who since December, 1988, had 
been executive vice president and chief financial officer for the Marshalls 
Inc. off-price retail chain. As the division's No. 2 executive, he will report 
to Chairman Harold D. Kahn. 
</P>
<P>
Sellers replaces Joseph Berzok, 55, who is retiring. Macy's South/Bullock's, 
based in Atlanta, consists of 48 department stores, including 20 Bullock's 
stores in Southern California. 
</P>
