<HEADLINE>
<P>
SOUTHERN SECTION BOYS' BASKETBALL PLAYOFFS; 
</P>
<P>
SOPHOMORES LEAD FAITH BAPTIST 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Led by sophomores Peter Rasmussen and Alex Estrada, Faith Baptist High rolled 
to a 74-64 win over second-seeded Montclair Prep in a Southern Section 1-A 
Division quarterfinal playoff game Tuesday night at Montclair Prep. 
</P>
<P>
Estrada, a guard, finished with a game-high 28 points and 11 rebounds. 
Rasmussen, a forward, had 21 points and 11 rebounds. 
</P>
<P>
Faith Baptist (17-10) played most of the game in a 2-3 zone defense, which 
Montclair Prep (19-5) failed to solve. The Mounties made just 25 of 79 (31.6%) 
field-goal attempts and five of 23 (21.7%) attempts from beyond the three-point 
arc. 
</P>
<P>
Faith Baptist also killed Montclair Prep at the free-throw line, outscoring the 
Mounties, 29-8. 
</P>
<P>
Notre Dame 76, Rancho Alamitos 71 -- Bobby DaCorsi scored 21 points to lead 
Notre Dame as the Knights upset host Rancho Alamitos in the quarterfinal round 
of the 3-A playoffs. 
</P>
<P>
Notre Dame jumped to a 17-point lead in the first quarter, but Rancho Alamitos 
cut the deficit 11 by the end of the half. 
</P>
<P>
Rancho Alamitos embarked on a 12-point run in the fourth quarter and cut the 
lead to four points, but the Knights capitalized on two free throws to seal the 
victory. 
</P>
<P>
Pasadena 69, Canyon 65 -- Pasadena's full-court press finally got the best of 
Canyon in the fourth quarter as the Bulldogs scored a come-from-behind victory 
in a 5-A game at Saugus High. 
</P>
<P>
Canyon led, 40-22, at halftime and, 54-45, after three quarters. But Pasadena 
ran off a 17-4 spurt to take a 62-57 lead with 3 minutes 24 seconds left. 
</P>
<P>
Santa Clara 78, Chaminade 42 -- Shon Tarver scored a game-high 35 points to 
lead top-seeded Santa Clara (22-0) in a 2-AA game at Calabasas High. 
</P>
<P>
Mark Mirkovich had 17 points and Mark Wiltshire had 10 for Chaminade (14-11), 
which had 10 rebounds in the game. 
</P>
<P>
Bethel Christian 73, Highland Hall 71 (OT) -- Leo Lett hit a 19-foot jump shot 
at the buzzer to upset the Small Schools' No. 3 seeded team and break Highland 
Hall's 19-game win streak in a game at Bethel Christian. 
</P>
<P>
Highland Hall forced overtime when Craig Ernst scored two of his 21 points with 
four seconds remaining. 
</P>
</TEXT>
