<P>
MORE TROOPS SENT TO TROUBLED KOSOVO 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Yugoslav government sent more troops and tanks into Kosovo province in an 
effort to control violent clashes between authorities and ethnic Albanians 
demanding greater autonomy. One Albanian was killed and 10 others were wounded 
in clashes with riot police in the town of Titova Mitrovica. Albanian students 
in Pristina announced that they will continue to boycott university classes to 
demand the resignation of the province's pro-Serbian leaders. 
</P>
