<HEADLINE>
<P>
METRO DIGEST LOCAL NEWS IN BRIEF: BOY, 14, ACCIDENTALLY KILLED BY BEST FRIEND 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A 14-year-old Long Beach boy was shot and killed by his best friend Tuesday as 
the two played with a shotgun authorities say was owned by the gang to which 
they both belonged. 
</P>
<P>
The boy was shot in the stomach about 11 a.m. in the 1100 block of Loma Vista 
Drive as he and his 16-year-old friend joked and took turns pointing the gun at 
each other and two other teen-agers watched, Detective William Collette said. 
</P>
<P>
The names of the youths were withheld. 
</P>
<P>
"It was a simple case of two kids playing with a gun and not knowing it was 
loaded," Collette said. The gun was owned by the gang and kept under a nearby 
apartment house, he said. The boy and his friend had brought the gun from its 
hiding place to show the others. 
</P>
<P>
The boy who allegedly fired the shot was booked on suspicion of murder and 
taken to Los Padrinos Juvenile Hall in Downey, Collette said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
