<HEADLINE>
<P>
'CHEERS' ON OPENING NIGHT OF TELEVISION FESTIVAL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Kirstie Alley, Ted Danson, and Shelley Long will discuss "Cheers" on the 
opening night of the Museum of Broadcasting's 7th annual Television Festival in 
the Los Angeles County Museum of Art's Leo S. Bing Theater on March 7. 
</P>
<P>
They will answer audience questions after a tape of the show's highlights is 
screened starting at 8 p.m. 
</P>
<P>
Other shows to be screened and to feature cast and crew members' comments 
during the festival include "Designing Women"on March 10, "The Young and the 
Restless" on March 15, and "CNN," which includes an appearance by Ted Turner, 
on March 21. The festival runs through March 24. 
</P>
<P>
Information: (213) 857-6010. 
</P>
</TEXT>
