<BYLINE>
<P>
By HEATHER SMALLEY 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
In another 3-A game: 
</P>
<P>
Sherman Oaks Notre Dame 76, Rancho Alamitos 71 -- Sherman Oaks Notre Dame High 
is going to the 3-A basketball semifinals for the first time. 
</P>
<P>
"At this point in time, we didn't think they were going to give up," Coach Mick 
Cady said. 
</P>
<P>
"They had won 20 games . . . but we're still not satisfied." 
</P>
<P>
Notre Dame (15-10) took a 27-17 first-quarter lead and was in control for much 
of the game. But with 2:32 left, Rancho Alamitos completed a 10-3 run and 
trimmed the Vaqueros' lead to 63-59. 
</P>
<P>
Rancho Alamitos forward Tony Cortez, the game's leading scorer with 23 points, 
fouled out less than a minute later, and that ended the Rancho Alamitos threat. 
</P>
<P>
"(Notre Dame was) a good team," said Rancho Alamitos Coach Eric Hamamoto, whose 
team finished with a 21-4 record. "They're taller, quicker and faster. But like 
I told my kids, I'd take our group over their group any time. 
</P>
<P>
"These guys are winners -- they're champions," he said. "We had kids that 
started the game on the bench out there (in the fourth quarter) and it was 
their guts. They never gave up." HEATHER SMALLEY 
</P>
