<P>
BOYS' ROUNDUP; 
</P>
<P>
VERDUM DEI'S PRESS FLATTENS SANTA MARGARITA BID, 56-52 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By TOM BIRSCHBACH 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
IRVINE 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Verbum Dei High School spoiled Santa Margarita's upset bid with a full-court 
press in the second half in a 56-52 victory in the quarterfinals of the 2-AA 
playoffs Tuesday night at Christ College Irvine. 
</P>
<P>
Santa Margarita, playing with no seniors against a team with a strong playoff 
record, led, 31-22, early in the third quarter. 
</P>
<P>
But Verbum Dei's press sparked a 19-2 run to take a 41-33 lead. 
</P>
<P>
Santa Margarita cut its deficit to 41-39 on Hayes Ferry's two free throws with 
4:09 remaining in the fourth quarter, but Verbum Dei, led by Mark Mitchell, 
pushed the lead to 53-42 lead. 
</P>
<P>
Mike Carpenter's three-point basket and Jeff Layne's inside scoring helped 
Santa Margarita close the gap to 56-52 in the final minute. 
</P>
<P>
Santa Margarita (14-13) was led by Layne's 15 points and five rebounds. Dan 
Bathey and Carpenter added 13 and 12 points, respectively. Mitchell and Zellie 
Hudson led Verbum Dei (13-12) with 20 and 15 points, respectively. TOM 
BIRSCHBACH 
</P>
</TEXT>
