<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY EARNINGS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
General Automation Inc.: The Anaheim computer company reported net income of 
$23,000 for the second fiscal quarter, contrasted with a loss of $989,000 for 
the corresponding period a year earlier. 
</P>
<P>
Revenue for the quarter ended Dec. 31 declined 19%, to $8.3 million from $10.2 
million in 1988. For the first six months, the company's net income totaled 
$77,000, contrasted with a loss of $1.9 million a year earlier. Sales dropped 
13%, to $17.3 million from $19.8 million. Leonard Mackenzie, GA's vice chairman 
and president, attributed the sales decline to "an exceedingly poor business 
climate throughout our industry during the latter part of 1989." 
