<P>
POPULATION OF TOKYO DECLINES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Wire Services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
TOKYO 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The population of Tokyo fell to an estimated 11.9 million as of Jan. 1, down 
0.11% from a year ago, its first decline in nine years, the metropolitan 
government said today. 
</P>
<P>
The population included 211,067 non-Japanese, among them 90,216 South Koreans, 
61,860 Chinese, 15,059 Americans and 10,898 Filipinos. 
</P>
<P>
A city official attributed the decline to a low birthrate and to people moving 
out of Tokyo because of the high cost of land and housing. 
</P>
</TEXT>
