</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
WASHINGTON 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Environmentalists accused White House Chief of Staff John H. Sununu today of 
leading President Bush astray on environmental policy, specifically charging 
Sununu with undercutting Administration efforts to protect wetlands, toughen 
clean air laws and fight global warming. 
</P>
<P>
In a letter to Bush, eight major environmental groups warned Sununu was 
undermining Bush's campaign promises to the American public to be a strong 
environmental President. 
</P>
<P>
"Mr. President, you articulated laudable environmental goals, but it appears 
your chief of staff is not committed to meeting them," the groups wrote. 
</P>
<P>
The environmentalists asked Bush for an emergency meeting to "clarify the 
direction in which you are headed on the environment." 
