<P>
BROTHER'S TASTES NOT FOR JANET 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Service Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
PENSACOLA, Fla. 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Janet Jackson shares her brother Michael's taste in rehearsal halls, but 
apparently not in main courses. 
</P>
<P>
When Michael Jackson rehearsed at the Pensacola Civic Center to prepare for his 
1988 "Bad" tour, his chef whipped up vegetarian entrees garnished with flowers 
from the Hilton Hotel florist shop, hotel employees said. 
</P>
<P>
But Janet Jackson, who is using the 10,000-seat Civic Center before starting 
her first solo national tour in Miami, has developed a fondness for Chicken 
Supreme sandwiches from McGuire's Irish Pub &amp; Brewery a few blocks from the 
Civic Center and Hilton, the Pensacola News Journal reported today. 
</P>
<P>
"From the day they arrived, Janet Jackson's roadies and sound crew have made us 
their second home," said Susi Lyon, promotion director for McGuire's. 
</P>
</TEXT>
